@NODE V14 "Latest news in v1.4"
@{b}Latest News in Version 1.4@{ub}

    Sorry for the long delay - but here`s the new version at least.
    If you look in the history you`ll notice that I removed the
    EmulationInfo screen aswell as the SuperNintendo logo at the
    top of the GUI. I`m not planning to include the EmulationInfo
    screen in further versions again - but I would like to include
    a logo in the GUI. Some guys requested a new one cooz the
    didn`t like the old - so please send me a new logo. It should
    be in the wb colors (4) or MWB colors (8). Please don`t use
    any other colors cooz I would have to add some remap code then
    and that would extend the executable size...So long, have fun
    with this version and look in the history to see what has
    changed. Greets, Andreas.

@ENDNODE
 
@NODE Introduction "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}

    Not so long time ago the sources of the popular Super Nintendo
    Emulator SNES9x were released. After a very short time the first
    Amiga 68k port appeared on the Internet. A PPC port followed
    the days. But both ports came without a GUI and that`s why this
    proggie is here :) Of course this version is early but it
    should work! (if not contact me ;-))

    You can use this GUI with all Amiga ports of SNES9x! Here are
    some features of the GUI:

    · supports the most of SNES9x options
    · has a small inbuild ROM editor
    · works with all Amiga SNES9x ports (including WarpSNES)
    · shows ROM size and memory type aswell as ROM name in an extra window
    · uses @{"MUI" LINK MUI}
    · is small, fast and highly optimized

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "Installation"
@{b}Installation@{ub}

    The installation requires my NewInstaller tool from Aminet
    (util/wb/NewInstaller1_5.lha). Download it and install SNES9xGUI!

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements "Requirements"
@{b}Requirements@{ub}

    · an Amiga :)
    · MUI v3.8+
    · asl.library v36+
    · one of the SNES9x Ports
    · SNES Roms

@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "Usage"
@{b}Usage@{ub}
    
    Usage isn`t very hard because the GUI features bubble help.
    If you don`t know what a gadget is good for hold the pointer
    some seconds infront of it and you`ll get good & fast
    online help ;-)

    Please note: Before you start the emulator you need to set
                 it in the Settings/SNES9x menu!! After that
                 you can use the emulator with all its features!

@ENDNODE

@NODE Errors "Errors"
@{b}Errors@{ub}

    There`re several errors that may appear during the usage
    of SNES9x GUI:

    · Cannot launch Emulator: You need to select the executable of
                              the emulator you`re using. Go to the
                              Settings/SNES9x menu and select it.
                              This messages also appears if the
                              specified executable does not exist on
                              your harddisk.

    · Cannot open ROM:        The ROM you specified isn`t present on
		              your harddisk.

    · Sound isn`t available:  You selected the Sound option
			      which isn`t present yet in
			      both emulators. It`s only in
		  	      the GUI because specifying
			      the option -nosound makes
			      the emulator faster!

    · IPS isn`t available:    The GUI doesn`t
			      support .IPS files yet cooz
			      I haven`t found any documentations
			      about this patch format. Hold
                              on! (BTW: If you got some docs
                              about IPS patching -> send them!)

@ENDNODE

